  "texts": [
    "For privacy reasons, patient-level data should be kept within an organizational firewall.",
    "Fortunately, many LLMs such as SDL2 are freely available for on-premises hosting, and many commercial models offer within-firewall cloud-based solutions.",
    "Combining LLMs with KEEPER enables our approach to be applied to any data within the CDM, including both administrative claims and EHRs.",
    "Our results on Test set 1 indicate that the performance of this combined method is comparable to human reviewers using KEEPER, and even to human reviewers with access to full patient charts.",
    "Although LLMs could theoretically be applied to entire charts, this is currently impractical with the models we evaluated, as the charts exceed the context window limit (e.g., 4000 tokens for Llama-2)."
  ],
